Ah, the rules. I suggest if you are planning to join, and have not already done so, that you read them. Why? Read on. ;)<br><br>
<br><br>
<dl><dt><b>· Three Strikes</b></dt><br><br>
<dd>Three Strikes and you're out. In other words, break three <i>important</i> rules, and you are no longer welcomed here. Don't get me wrong— everyone makes mistakes, but if you do something bad on purpose, and don't even apologize to whomever you have caused the problem(s) for, there <b>will</b> be concequences.</dd><br><br>
<br><br>
<dl><dt><b>· Respect</b></dt><br><br>
<dd>C'mon, you <i>know</i> this one. ;) Respect is a must. Actually, out of character respect is not an option, but a requirement. In character respect, on the other hand, is up to you. Just don't abuse that option. Please. x_X;</dd><br><br>
<br><br>
<dl><dt><b>· Characters</b></dt><br><br>
<dd>A character's appearance is completely up to you. Unlike other RPGs— yes, your character can be a shapeshifter (ask permission first though, in an OOC forum), he/she can have wings, strange colors, markings… the whole enchilada. HOWEVER: you may have <i>two</i> and two characters only, unless you have been given permission to roleplay more by the Admins.</dd><br><br>
<br><br>
<dl><dt><b>· Pups</b></dt><br><br>
<dd>Pups, cubs, whatever you care to call them, are an option. Though it is unrealistic, the setting is, too, and the climates would fit nicely with this. Breeding season is during <b>January to April</b>, and <b>July to Ocober</b>. ANY wolf— be it a leader or not, must ask permission from the Admins before making their announcement public. Gestation lasts about 60 days, but you may, if you wish, make it only two weeks (or more), but must roleplay it out to appear as 2 months.Litters constist of 1-5 pups,either gender,and can stay with their parents for 2 R(ole)P(lay)T(ime) months.</dd><br><br>
<br><br>
<dl><dt><b>· Leaving</b></dt><br><br>
<dd>If you plan to leave, tell us (either privately or on the forums) and we will remove you char. from the rank listings. UNLESS: you decided to give you character to another RPer, in which case, all IC information will remain the same.</dd><br><br>
<br><br>
<dl><dt><b>· Golden Rule</b></dt><br><br>
<dd>And most importantly… enjoy your stay!</dd><br><br>
